# UI and Component Rules

Rules for using Base UI / shadcn components, structuring pages, and protecting base components.

## Base UI Over Radix

This project uses **Base UI** with shadcn (not Radix UI). Follow Base UI syntax only.

- **Use `render`, not `asChild`.** Base UI uses the `render` prop to customize the root element; Radix uses `asChild`. Never use `asChild` on components from `components/ui/`.
- When composing triggers, buttons, or custom root elements, pass a React element to `render`, e.g. `render={<Button variant="outline" />}`.
- If unsure, open the component in `components/ui/` and confirm the actual prop name (e.g. `render`) and supported props before writing code.

## Page Structure (Next.js / React)

When **creating or refactoring a page** (App Router page, layout, or route):

1. **Use the Vercel React best practices skill** (`.cursor/skills/vercel-react-best-practices`): read the skill and apply the relevant rules for data fetching, waterfalls, Suspense, bundle size, and rendering.
2. Structure the page accordingly (e.g. parallel data fetching, strategic Suspense boundaries, minimal serialization at RSC boundaries).

## Use Only Existing Components and Their Real Props

- **Always use the components that exist** in this project (e.g. under `components/ui/` and any project-specific components). Do not invent or assume components that are not in the codebase.
- **Before using a component, check its definition**: open the component file and see which props/attributes it accepts (including Base UI primitives’ props). Use only those props and attributes.
- **Do not hallucinate props or attributes.** If a component does not accept a prop (e.g. it has no `asChild`), do not use it. Wrong examples: using `asChild` on Base UI components, or adding props that are not in the component’s type definition.
- When in doubt, read the component source in `components/ui/` (and any wrapper) and match the usage to the actual API.

## Base Components (components/ui/) — No Edits Without Permission

- **Do not change files under `components/ui/`** unless the user explicitly asks to modify a base component (e.g. “change the Button variants”, “add a new Dialog prop”).
- **Compose, don’t edit.** Achieve the desired UI by composing existing components in feature components (e.g. under `components/` but outside `ui/`). Do not edit base components to fit a single use case.
- **If a task would require editing a base component:** stop and ask: “This would require changing [ComponentName] in `components/ui/`. Should I modify it, or do you prefer a wrapper/alternative?” Do not modify `components/ui/` without explicit approval.

## Summary

| Topic | Rule |
|-------|------|
| Base UI vs Radix | Use `render`, never `asChild`. Follow Base UI API only. |
| Pages | When creating/refactoring pages, use vercel-react-best-practices skill for structure and performance. |
| Component usage | Use only existing components; always check the component file for real props; never hallucinate props (e.g. no `asChild`). |
| components/ui/ | Do not edit base components unless the user explicitly asks; compose in other components or ask before changing. |
